      <p class="text-lg" style="max-width:none"><strong>Recovery</strong> restores the database to a consistent state after a crash. The key mechanism is <strong>write-ahead logging</strong> (WAL): before any data page is modified on disk, the change is first recorded in a log. On crash recovery, the log replays committed changes (redo) and undoes uncommitted ones (undo).</p>
